{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":15708,"name":"","username":"NiteLordz","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/e8c25b/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-01-16T15:45:43.125Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI have been looking thru the forums, and was wondering if anyone has attempted to create a volumetric renderer.  I am interested in implementing the Horizon Dawn Volumetric Clouds system, and if anyone has a head start on it, would jump in on it, otherwise, would will start from scratch.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks much\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-16T15:45:43.125Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":229,"reads":65,"readers_count":64,"score":1155.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2713,"topic_slug":"volumetric-rendering","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":15711,"name":"","username":"dragonCASTjosh","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/dragoncastjosh/{size}/774_2.png","created_at":"2017-01-16T21:05:39.779Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI think there has been a few experiments in the community on volumetric rendering but i dont think there is anything game ready. Once i start making progress on my long list of features i will eventually hit Volumetrics but likely not anytime soon. Once i get to it i will likely based my implementation upon \u003ca href=\"http://www.frostbite.com/2015/08/physically-based-unified-volumetric-rendering-in-frostbite/\"\u003ehttp://www.frostbite.com/2015/08/physically-based-unified-volumetric-rendering-in-frostbite/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-16T21:05:39.779Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":64,"readers_count":63,"score":22.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2713,"topic_slug":"volumetric-rendering","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://www.frostbite.com/2015/08/physically-based-unified-volumetric-rendering-in-frostbite/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Physically-based \u0026 Unified Volumetric Rendering in Frostbite - Frostbite","clicks":66}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":284,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19374,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-07-12T16:00:28.653Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAny progress with this?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-12T16:00:28.653Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":57,"readers_count":56,"score":11.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2713,"topic_slug":"volumetric-rendering","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19376,"name":"","username":"godan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/godan/{size}/49_2.png","created_at":"2017-07-12T17:31:33.300Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eFor IOGRAM, I hacked together a material/shader combo that requires a box and a 3d texture. The shader renders the volume texture using some nice tricks. The advantage of this is that it fits in well with the existing render pipeline (i.e. you can easily control visibility/occlusion). \u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/a8a342094c68cbc11b940baf6121251ec96396fa.jpg\" width=\"690\" height=\"370\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, I wrote some code to combine sequences of images in to a single 3d texture, and even modify the 3d texture directly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere are the sources: \u003ca href=\"https://gist.github.com/danhambleton/f318a91405c36aef15dc4cda4e93c451\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e[1]\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/MeshGeometry/IogramSource/blob/master/Components/Graphics_Texture3D.cpp\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e[2]\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eoriginal post: \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/volume-shader-for-3d-textures/2966\" class=\"inline-onebox-loading\"\u003ehttps://discourse.urho3d.io/t/volume-shader-for-3d-textures/2966\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-12T17:32:35.704Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":51.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2713,"topic_slug":"volumetric-rendering","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://gist.github.com/danhambleton/f318a91405c36aef15dc4cda4e93c451","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Volume render for 3D Texture · GitHub","clicks":9},{"url":"https://github.com/MeshGeometry/IogramSource/blob/master/Components/Graphics_Texture3D.cpp","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"IogramSource/Graphics_Texture3D.cpp at master · MeshGeometry/IogramSource · GitHub","clicks":7},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/volume-shader-for-3d-textures/2966","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Volume shader for 3D Textures","clicks":6}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19631,"name":"","username":"Bananaft","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/bananaft/{size}/222_2.png","created_at":"2017-07-27T09:59:54.716Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI’ve made a raymarching demo with some cool optimizations.\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"2403\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/bananaft/40/222_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/3d-fractals-demo/2403\"\u003e3D fractals demo\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca class=\"badge-wrapper  bullet\" href=\"/c/showcase/projects/12\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-parent-bg\" style=\"background-color: #F1592A;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-bg\" style=\"background-color: #808281;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category clear-badge\" title=\"Announcements and news updates to your projects using Urho3D.\"\u003eProjects\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cblockquote\u003e\n    Lately I was playing with raymarching and 3d-fractals. I came up with the method to optimize raymarching and implemented it in Urho. I also added volumetric light scattering for point and spot lights. Taking from this demo: \u003ca href=\"http://blog.mmacklin.com/2010/05/29/in-scattering-demo/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eblog.mmacklin.com/2010/05/29/in-scattering-demo/\u003c/a\u003e and using some ugly hackery to make it work with finite attenuation lights (it uses inverse square fore light attenuation ). \nRequires modern GPU. \nScreenshots and download: \n\u003ca href=\"https://bananaft.itch.io/yedomaglobula\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ebananaft.itch.io/yedomaglobula\u003c/a\u003e \nFollow me: \u003ca href=\"https://twitter.com/Bananaft\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ehttps://t…\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHorizon’s cloud system would be super cool to play with. Hovever, it is super expencive, as my favorite part from their paper suggests:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/c63662311cea5c3a26cdf36ca722fe954d339d61.png\" width=\"629\" height=\"286\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd both Horizon and \u003ca href=\"https://developer.unigine.com/ru/devlog/20170206-unigine-2.4\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eUnigine\u003c/a\u003e are using either Temporal AA or some other form of reprojection to spread samples over time.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-27T10:05:42.391Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":52,"readers_count":51,"score":40.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2713,"topic_slug":"volumetric-rendering","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://developer.unigine.com/ru/devlog/20170206-unigine-2.4","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"UNIGINE 2.4: New Multi-Layered Volumetric Clouds, New Terrain, Oil Refinery Demo - Unigine Developer","clicks":14},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/3d-fractals-demo/2403","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"3D fractals demo","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":165,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":"downloaded local copies of images","can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[15708,15711,19374,19376,19631]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,2137],[2,2136],[3,1960],[4,1959],[5,1945]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7062,"title":"Is WebGL2.0 \u0026 GLES3.0 being supported in the near future?","fancy_title":"Is WebGL2.0 \u0026amp; GLES3.0 being supported in the near future?","slug":"is-webgl2-0-gles3-0-being-supported-in-the-near-future","posts_count":2,"reply_count":0,"highest_post_number":2,"image_url":null,"created_at":"2021-11-23T09:04:28.802Z","last_posted_at":"2021-11-23T21:44:08.088Z","bumped":true,"bumped_at":"2021-11-23T21:44:08.088Z","archetype":"regular","unseen":false,"pinned":false,"unpinned":null,"visible":true,"closed":false,"archived":false,"bookmarked":null,"liked":null,"tags_descriptions":{},"like_count":1,"views":199,"category_id":16,"featured_link":null,"has_accepted_answer":false,"posters":[{"extras":null,"description":"Original Poster","user":{"id":1490,"username":"Sunc"